main event: Two objects were observed in the sky over Kansas City, Missouri on May 23, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were reported to be moving at incredible speed in a straight line formation., There was no audible sound from the objects., Witnesses noted that the objects had a bright, silvery appearance., The sighting lasted for about 4 minutes., The Kansas City Police were initially unsure if it was a military exercise.
witness description: Kansas City Police reported the sighting.
